The paper deals with designing an algorithm to compute sparse graphs for the traveling salesman problem (TSP) based on frequency quadrilaterals. This involves computational geometry, graph theory, and optimization, which are all relevant to the sub-categories of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), and cs.LG (Machine Learning). However, since the paper focuses more on the algorithmic and optimization aspects, cs.DS and cs.DM are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.AI, cs.CG, and cs.LG.
